The gift of being known and understood is I am quite sure a rare thing and in particular with "misunderstood" people.
I believe it is possible for another soul to become a surrogate for what ever reason you may need them. They stand with you..beside you
Unconditional acceptance provides a freedom to move forward in relating on a soul level. So much of us is veiled,obscuring our transparency.
Another soul can "guide" you through....mysteriously...only god knows how this happens but some people just have abilities
Hippies were souls that were freed of mental baggage...with all of its fallout, that time did allow for a certain type of peace and freedom
To get hung up on rules and societal minutia, allowing it to dictate how you think and live is NOT living in freedom, but in bondage
The brazen serpent had or has the job of taking on the sting of sins. Jesus was like a brazen serpent and some people are as well I believe
The serpent on the pole,or Jesus on the healed when people looked  on it with hope faith and belief in him.It wasn't the snake, but belief
So for us..there is power in believing...it's a universal "god" power...part of gods universal rules underpinning everything
So as wounded healers we don't claim credit for any works, but people look to us in hope as we act in godly ways to others...we are used...
It is a counterintuitive paradox that healing can come through the most cursed thing...a snake...the venom becomes anti venom
So a problem now occurs in the interpretation of what gods work is. Jesus was quite clear, but still the central "love" concept is obscured
So why don't people just get out there and do good things? I guess they aren't Jesus hands and they aren't doing gods will.Too busy arguing.
Ministry is the pouring out of your self and as you pour,,more gets poured in...you get tired, but not until you have done a lot of good
The concept of overflow it neat...gods love is poured into you, or you accept it, and what spills over is ministry. Doesn't happen that way
Healing is healing of the broken soul. We need others to make much of it happen.."I need some one with a human touch" #notspicegirls
There is a certain "lightness" of soul where everything but love has been stripped off. So, so few are so light as that. They are happy
It's not "ignorance is bliss" either because simplicity of soul allows for decisions unhindered by baggage. Transparency is a start
The Christian church????  It's always have a rough go in terms of transparency..but there is always a remnant..hope...outside unfortunately
War ships....
